Why are we sitting with Magnolia Barnard?

242
00:12:57.402 --> 00:12:59.279
Because without Bob. I need her help.

243
00:12:59.737 --> 00:13:03.783
Plus. Magnolia is awesome.
She's pretty and smart and nice.

244
00:13:03.866 --> 00:13:05.451
I know. it's annoying.

245
00:13:06.286 --> 00:13:07.120
Hey.

246
00:13:07.203 --> 00:13:10.123
- Make room for Patty and her girlfriend.
- Friend. who's a girl.

247
00:13:10.206 --> 00:13:11.332
That's what I said.

248
00:13:13.710 --> 00:13:15.169
Dixie's the worst. right?

249
00:13:15.253 --> 00:13:18.506
And she's living in my house.
It's a total disastrophe.

250
00:13:18.589 --> 00:13:20.633
Anyway. let's talk about
your pageant issues.

251
00:13:21.175 --> 00:13:23.136
What you have is an image problem.

252
00:13:23.219 --> 00:13:25.138
You need to worry about the pageant board.

253
00:13:25.221 --> 00:13:27.390
We have to get them thinking
you're a good person.

254
00:13:27.473 --> 00:13:29.726
someone who's deserving
of the Miss Magic Jesus crown.

255
00:13:30.268 --> 00:13:33.146
- So. how do we do that?
<i>- </i>We need a multi-pronged approach.

256
00:13:33.229 --> 00:13:36.232
First. we need to prove to them that
you didn't send out that picture of Dixie.

257
00:13:36.316 --> 00:13:37.775
Figure out who hacked your phone.

258
00:13:37.859 --> 00:13:39.777
I could ask the guys
in Computer Club for help.

259
00:13:39.861 --> 00:13:40.695
Great idea.

260
00:13:40.778 --> 00:13:44.157
In the meantime. we need to present you
as some one who's kind. charitable.

261
00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:46.951
The kind of person who never would've
cyber-bullied in the first place.

262
00:13:47.660 --> 00:13:50.788
Hmm... Do you have any philanthropy
on your resume?

263
00:13:50.872 --> 00:13:53.249
Because most of the main competitors
for Miss Magic Jesus

264
00:13:53.333 --> 00:13:56.085
have earned at least $5.000
for their respective charities.

265
00:13:56.169 --> 00:13:57.170
Shit. really?

266
00:13:57.253 --> 00:14:00.298
You should choose a cause that has
something to do with your platform.

267
00:14:00.715 --> 00:14:02.675
- Do you have one yet?
- A platform? Yeah.

268
00:14:02.759 --> 00:14:05.470
It's something about being fat
and then not being fat.

269
00:14:05.553 --> 00:14:08.973
Perfect. Awareness of eating
and body dysmorphic disorders.

270
00:14:09.057 --> 00:14:13.686
You can raise money for the Northern
Georgia Eating Disorder Recovery Clinic.

271
00:14:13.770 --> 00:14:17.190
- Oh. my God! You're really good at this.
- Now. we just need an event.

272
00:14:20.443 --> 00:14:22.362
- Bikini car wash?
- Played out.

273
00:14:23.404 --> 00:14:25.365
- Dog adoption?
- Yawn.

274
00:14:26.491 --> 00:14:28.201
Bikini dog wash?

275
00:14:28.785 --> 00:14:32.163
- Bikini dog wash?
- Bikini dog wash!

276
00:14:32.246 --> 00:14:34.707
Bikini dog wash!

277
00:14:35.124 --> 00:14:38.044
Bikinis for girls recovering
from eating disorders...

278
00:14:38.127 --> 00:14:40.421
- isn't that sort of...?
- Let's do it. This weekend?

279
00:14:40.505 --> 00:14:43.341
Amazing. Patty. you talk to
the Computer Club about your phone.

280
00:14:43.424 --> 00:14:46.260
I'll talk to Student Council about
getting a permit for this dog wash.

281
00:14:46.344 --> 00:14:50.390
- And Nonnie. can you make a flyer?
- She'll totally do it. Right. Nonnie?

282
00:14:50.473 --> 00:14:53.393
- Whatever you say.
- Okay. perfect.

283
00:14:53.476 --> 00:14:56.646
Okay. now that that's sorted.
how are we gonna get the word out?

284
00:14:56.729 --> 00:14:58.731
First things first.
'cause it's all about promotion.

285
00:14:59.273 --> 00:15:01.025
Patty's losing her mind.

286
00:15:01.526 --> 00:15:03.361
"Oh. Magnolia's so awesome.

287
00:15:03.444 --> 00:15:05.822
Magnolia's so everything."

288
00:15:07.281 --> 00:15:08.449
What's wrong?

289
00:15:08.825 --> 00:15:11.077
Everything is always about Patty.

290
00:15:11.744 --> 00:15:14.038
I'm such an idiot.
I should have known you were gay.

291
00:15:15.206 --> 00:15:16.457
Wait. what?

292
00:15:16.541 --> 00:15:18.501
Everyone's saying
you and Patty are a couple.

293
00:15:18.584 --> 00:15:20.336
What the hell. Choi?

294
00:15:20.545 --> 00:15:22.922
Did I seem gay
when your tongue was in my mouth?

295
00:15:23.005 --> 00:15:26.175
No. but whenever we're together.
all you do is talk about her.

296
00:15:26.259 --> 00:15:27.677
That is so not true.

297
00:15:27.760 --> 00:15:30.847
It is true. And if you're into Patty.
it's totally cool.

298
00:15:30.930 --> 00:15:33.599
but please. just be honest.

299
00:15:33.683 --> 00:15:36.978
I am not into Patty.
I'm super annoyed at her.

300
00:15:37.061 --> 00:15:39.856
Six months ago. Magnolia
wouldn't give her the time of day.

301
00:15:39.939 --> 00:15:42.650
I'm the one who was there when
she ran out of Weight Watcher's points.

302
00:15:42.733 --> 00:15:45.027
when she ate birthday cake
out of the trash.

303
00:15:45.111 --> 00:15:46.112
You sound jealous.

304
00:15:46.195 --> 00:15:47.363
Seriously?

305
00:15:47.447 --> 00:15:51.325
I just got out of a situation where I was
more into someone than they were into me.

306
00:15:51.409 --> 00:15:55.329
So. when you figure your shit out.
let me know.

307
00:16:06.382 --> 00:16:08.092
- Gentlemen.
- What?

308
00:16:08.176 --> 00:16:09.343
Oh. hi.

309
00:16:09.427 --> 00:16:13.139
I need your help. Somebody hacked my phone
and leaked those pictures of Dixie.

310
00:16:13.514 --> 00:16:16.851
- I need you to figure out who.
- Wait. what's in it for us?

311
00:16:17.685 --> 00:16:18.603
Uh...

312
00:16:19.020 --> 00:16:20.104
What do you want?

313
00:16:20.188 --> 00:16:21.856
- A date.
- With all of us.

314
00:16:21.939 --> 00:16:23.900
Collectively. Three.

315
00:16:25.359 --> 00:16:28.905
Gross. You can't just leverage me
like that. it's wrong.

316
00:16:28.988 --> 00:16:32.492
Okay. Hey. was it wrong when you
showed your boobs to Donald Choi?

317
00:16:34.327 --> 00:16:36.204
Yeah. it's a small town. people talk.

318
00:16:36.746 --> 00:16:37.788
This was a bad idea.

319
00:16:37.872 --> 00:16:40.208
Hey. mystery girl. maybe I can help you.

320
00:16:41.542 --> 00:16:45.046
Oh. no. That burnout over there
has no idea how to trace a hacker.

321
00:16:45.129 --> 00:16:47.840
Loser. what's it like to have sex
with a USB port?

322
00:16:49.800 --> 00:16:51.052
Christian. how do you...?

323
00:16:51.135 --> 00:16:54.889
I've traveled the world with my dad.
spent most of my time in Internet cafes.

324
00:16:55.306 --> 00:16:57.767
I met this guy in Brussels.
he took me under his wing.

325
00:16:57.850 --> 00:16:59.143
taught me all about the dark web.

326
00:16:59.227 --> 00:17:01.395
So. you can help me?

327
00:17:01.479 --> 00:17:02.355
For a price.

328
00:17:04.357 --> 00:17:07.276
- You're just as bad as they are.
- Not like that.

329
00:17:08.361 --> 00:17:10.196
I need your help with something too.

330
00:17:13.199 --> 00:17:14.367
I can trust you. right?

331
00:17:16.327 --> 00:17:17.161
I'm in trouble.

332
00:17:17.245 --> 00:17:21.791
Last Saturday night.
I. uh. got arrested with drugs in my car.

333
00:17:22.917 --> 00:17:25.503
My mom thinks I'm dealing. which I'm not.

334
00:17:25.753 --> 00:17:27.880
And she wants my lawyer to throw the case.

335
00:17:27.964 --> 00:17:30.091
because she thinks some jail time
would do me good.

336
00:17:30.174 --> 00:17:31.676
That sucks.

337
00:17:32.093 --> 00:17:34.262
But I'm not sure how I can help you.

338
00:17:34.345 --> 00:17:36.556
My lawyer is your pageant coach.

339
00:17:37.473 --> 00:17:40.476
I need you to help me convince him
to keep me out of jail.

340
00:17:40.935 --> 00:17:42.353
You guys are close. right?

341
00:17:44.146 --> 00:17:45.481
Not at the moment.

342
00:17:46.065 --> 00:17:48.276
Besides. Bob would never throw a case.
It's unethical.

343
00:17:48.943 --> 00:17:50.778
Maybe you don't know him
as well as you think.

344
00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:53.906
He definitely agreed to do it.
I heard my parents arguing about it.

345
00:17:55.366 --> 00:17:58.035
So. can you talk to him for me?

346
00:17:59.078 --> 00:18:00.913
I'm not sure he would listen.

347
00:18:00.997 --> 00:18:03.416
Then I'm not sure if I can help you.

348
00:18:07.044 --> 00:18:10.715
<i>Christian was my only hope
at getting back into Miss Magic Jesus.</i>

349
00:18:10.798 --> 00:18:14.260
<i>So even if it was a long shot.
I had to take my chances.</i>

350
00:18:14.343 --> 00:18:15.636
Christian. wait!

351
00:18:19.890 --> 00:18:21.350
<i>With a charge so small.</i>

352
00:18:21.434 --> 00:18:24.562
<i>Christian was likely to get off
with a slap on the wrist.</i>

353
00:18:24.645 --> 00:18:27.690
<i>which would leave me
in the doghouse with Coralee.</i>

354
00:18:28.065 --> 00:18:32.361
<i>If I wanted Christian in jail.
I'd have to bat Barnard's beehive.</i>

355
00:18:32.903 --> 00:18:35.615
<i>Luckily. I had an ace up my sleeve.</i>

356
00:18:38.034 --> 00:18:39.952
Patty. what are you doing?

357
00:18:40.036 --> 00:18:42.788
Look. Bob. I know you're mad at me.
but I need your help.

358
00:18:43.205 --> 00:18:46.959
La. la. la! No. no. no! I have no time.
I'm on my way to a meeting.

359
00:18:47.043 --> 00:18:49.754
Is it true you agreed to throw
Christian's case for his mom?

360
00:18:50.379 --> 00:18:53.549
Why is that any of your business?

361
00:18:53.633 --> 00:18:56.302
Because Christian said he can help me
figure out who hacked my phone.

362
00:18:56.385 --> 00:18:58.429
but only if I convince you
to keep him out of jail.

363
00:18:58.512 --> 00:19:00.097
I am his attorney.

364
00:19:00.181 --> 00:19:03.309
Obviously. I will do everything I can
to defend him.

365
00:19:04.018 --> 00:19:05.978
That's not what his mom said.

366
00:19:06.145 --> 00:19:08.439
He overheard her saying that
you agreed to throw the case.

367
00:19:08.522 --> 00:19:10.775
I had to. because of you.

368
00:19:11.651 --> 00:19:13.944
- Wait. what?
- It's a favor for Coralee.

369
00:19:14.570 --> 00:19:17.782
It's my best chance at getting her back
after the stunt you pulled.

370
00:19:17.865 --> 00:19:23.788
So. if you'll excuse me. I have to go
swallow my pride and compromise my morals

371
00:19:23.871 --> 00:19:25.623
because of your bad judgment.

372
00:19:26.666 --> 00:19:29.377
Wait... Wait. so you're not gonna help me?

373
00:19:29.460 --> 00:19:30.920
What about Miss Magic Jesus?

374
00:19:31.003 --> 00:19:34.548
Maybe you should have thought of that
before you decided to blow up my life.

375
00:19:37.968 --> 00:19:40.721
Just so you know.
Brick thinks you don't care about him.

376
00:19:41.138 --> 00:19:42.515
Excuse me?

377
00:19:42.973 --> 00:19:44.558
After you left the school. we talked.

378
00:19:44.642 --> 00:19:47.186
He told me that all he wants is
for you to pay attention to him

379
00:19:47.269 --> 00:19:50.231
and you haven't even bothered to show up
to one of his wrestling matches.

380
00:19:52.066 --> 00:19:53.275
He said that?

381
00:19:54.068 --> 00:19:55.027
I...

382
00:19:55.361 --> 00:19:56.779
I got to go see him.

383
00:19:58.280 --> 00:20:00.449
<i>If there's one thing
Coralee and I would agree on.</i>

384
00:20:00.533 --> 00:20:04.578
<i>it's that Brick was more important.
Barnard would have to wait.</i>

385
00:20:12.128 --> 00:20:15.423
- What in the hell are you doing?
- My community service.

386
00:20:15.506 --> 00:20:19.468
I got caught texting and driving.
so they assigned me here.

387
00:20:19.552 --> 00:20:21.303
I mean. that.

388
00:20:21.387 --> 00:20:23.806
Oh. the director asked me
to paint over the slurs.

389
00:20:23.889 --> 00:20:26.892
I'm pretty sure he meant
on the outside of the building.

390
00:20:31.188 --> 00:20:32.982
I can't do anything right.

391
00:20:34.108 --> 00:20:36.068
Honey. it's just paint.

392
00:20:36.152 --> 00:20:37.319
No. I am a mess.

393
00:20:38.529 --> 00:20:41.866
My girlfriend just broke up with me
because I slept with someone else's mom.

394
00:20:42.324 --> 00:20:44.785
Well. why'd you cheat? Were you not happy?

395
00:20:45.911 --> 00:20:48.581
I don't know.
I didn't really think about it.

396
00:20:49.373 --> 00:20:52.001
Did she not make you laugh?
Could you talk to her?

397
00:20:52.084 --> 00:20:54.253
All I know is. I hurt her
and I want to make it right.

398
00:20:55.379 --> 00:20:58.507
Sweetie. sometimes you can't
un-ring a bell.

399
00:20:59.759 --> 00:21:03.554
I'm screwed. Bob hates me and if
I don't figure out who hacked my phone.

400
00:21:03.637 --> 00:21:05.264
I'm never gonna get into Miss Magic Jesus.

401
00:21:05.347 --> 00:21:07.391
Relax. One thing at a time.

402
00:21:07.975 --> 00:21:11.520
We'll work on your philanthropy
and then we'll work on clearing your name.

403
00:21:11.604 --> 00:21:15.107
All thanks to Magnolia Barnard's
multi-pronged plan.

404
00:21:15.649 --> 00:21:16.776
Is something wrong?

405
00:21:17.485 --> 00:21:18.319
Uh...

406
00:21:18.402 --> 00:21:22.490
At lunch... you just let Magnolia
boss me around.

407
00:21:22.948 --> 00:21:25.910
I'm your best friend.
now you're just gonna up and ditch me

408
00:21:25.993 --> 00:21:27.661
because Magnolia Barnard is so awesome.

409
00:21:27.745 --> 00:21:28.788
No. Nonnie.

410
00:21:28.871 --> 00:21:32.374
Look. no matter what happens.
you're still my number one.

411
00:21:33.167 --> 00:21:34.084
Good.

412
00:21:35.252 --> 00:21:39.006
Because I think the flyer I made for you
is also pretty freaking awesome.

413
00:21:39.298 --> 00:21:42.593
Where'd you get
all those pictures of girls in bikinis?

414
00:21:43.219 --> 00:21:46.430
Uh. from a website.
which I've never been to before.

415
00:21:48.057 --> 00:21:49.975
God. I wish I looked that good
in a bikini.

416
00:21:50.601 --> 00:21:51.811
Have you seen yourself?

417
00:21:51.894 --> 00:21:53.479
Yeah. I'm thinner.

418
00:21:53.562 --> 00:21:57.191
I still have to lose 100 pounds before I'd
even think about getting into a bikini.

419
00:21:57.274 --> 00:21:59.944
Stop. Your body is banging.

420
00:22:00.027 --> 00:22:02.738
I'm still not gonna put on a bikini
in front of other people.

421
00:22:03.656 --> 00:22:05.241
Uh. you kind of have to.

422
00:22:06.075 --> 00:22:09.078
It's your event. It won't look good
if you don't participate.

423
00:22:09.161 --> 00:22:11.914
- This is a catastrophe.
- It's not nuclear war.

424
00:22:11.997 --> 00:22:13.040
I'll help you.

425
00:22:14.291 --> 00:22:16.418
- Patty told you that?
- Is it true?

426
00:22:16.710 --> 00:22:18.128
You think I don't care about you?

427
00:22:18.212 --> 00:22:19.672
What am I supposed to think?

428
00:22:19.755 --> 00:22:22.800
You don't ask me anything
about my life. my friends. school.

429
00:22:22.883 --> 00:22:25.678
- I don't know what to ask.
- You are proving my point.

430
00:22:26.345 --> 00:22:29.056
Okay. yeah. we're nothing alike.
but I'm still your son.

431
00:22:29.139 --> 00:22:32.101
so you can't just... blow me off.

432
00:22:34.019 --> 00:22:35.062
Oh. my God.

433
00:22:36.272 --> 00:22:37.439
Oh. my God.

434
00:22:38.148 --> 00:22:39.400
I'm doing it to you.

435
00:22:40.234 --> 00:22:41.652
The same thing he did to me.

436
00:22:41.735 --> 00:22:42.736
Who?

437
00:22:43.487 --> 00:22:45.948
My own dad.

438
00:22:46.031 --> 00:22:48.951
He wanted a wide receiver
and instead he got Henry Higgins.

439
00:22:49.785 --> 00:22:51.662
Higgins. is that like
a baseball player. or...?

440
00:22:51.745 --> 00:22:56.292
Lord. no!
It is only the most iconic character...

441
00:22:56.375 --> 00:22:58.502
Okay. look. it doesn't matter.

442
00:23:00.629 --> 00:23:01.755
I'm sorry.

443
00:23:02.256 --> 00:23:05.801
I never meant to make
you feel the way I felt.

444
00:23:07.344 --> 00:23:10.556
And I'm so proud of you
and your accomplishments.

445
00:23:10.931 --> 00:23:12.516
How can I make it up to you?

446
00:23:14.143 --> 00:23:17.688
For starters. you can tell me
what happened between you and mom.

447
00:23:28.490 --> 00:23:32.077
Decades ago. before you were born.

448
00:23:33.245 --> 00:23:36.498
I had an affair...

449
00:23:37.875 --> 00:23:39.877
with my pageant-coaching mentor.

450
00:23:39.960 --> 00:23:44.465
Your mom just found out about it
and she needs some time to think.

451
00:23:45.841 --> 00:23:46.842
Do you regret it?

452
00:23:47.259 --> 00:23:49.595
One-million percent.

453
00:23:49.929 --> 00:23:53.182
It was... It was a stupid. stupid mistake.

454
00:23:55.893 --> 00:23:57.144
Did you love her?

455
00:23:59.438 --> 00:24:03.108
I don't know.
Maybe. but I loved your mother more.

456
00:24:03.192 --> 00:24:04.443
Then why'd you cheat?

457
00:24:08.238 --> 00:24:12.117
It was a certain time.
it was a certain place.

458
00:24:12.201 --> 00:24:15.996
Stella Rose and I had mutual interests.
mutual goals.

459
00:24:17.373 --> 00:24:21.085
Also. there was a lot of drink
and she liked it rough

460
00:24:21.168 --> 00:24:23.796
and wanted to try some stuff
that your mama just wouldn't.

461
00:24:23.879 --> 00:24:27.257
Stop!
I did not want to know that.

462
00:24:27.341 --> 00:24:28.342
You asked.

463
00:24:28.425 --> 00:24:30.844
No. I was asking if you and mom
thought you could work it out.

464
00:24:31.845 --> 00:24:33.180
I am trying.

465
00:24:34.723 --> 00:24:35.557
How?

466
00:24:35.975 --> 00:24:42.147
The next time you talk to your mom.
tell her I'm doing what she asked.

467
00:24:42.231 --> 00:24:45.859
because I'm willing to do
whatever it takes to get her back. okay?

468
00:24:47.486 --> 00:24:48.612
Whatever. Dad.

469
00:24:59.832 --> 00:25:00.874
Patty?

470
00:25:01.834 --> 00:25:02.876
You okay?

471
00:25:04.294 --> 00:25:06.046
You've been in there for a while.

472
00:25:11.343 --> 00:25:12.261
Patty?

473
00:25:14.346 --> 00:25:15.389
I'm...

474
00:25:16.473 --> 00:25:17.683
I'm coming in.

475
00:25:20.519 --> 00:25:22.604
Oh. my God! What's wrong?

476
00:25:23.605 --> 00:25:24.565
I'm gross.

477
00:25:24.648 --> 00:25:26.692
No. you're not. you're beautiful.

478
00:25:26.775 --> 00:25:28.068
Mm-mm. I'm ugly.

479
00:25:28.861 --> 00:25:32.364
On the outside and on the inside.
I hurt Bob. I hurt you.

480
00:25:32.448 --> 00:25:33.699
I forgive you.

481
00:25:33.782 --> 00:25:35.784
Yeah. you shouldn't and he hasn't.

482
00:25:35.868 --> 00:25:37.369
Patty. stop!

483
00:25:37.995 --> 00:25:39.663
When you're mad at yourself
about something.

484
00:25:39.747 --> 00:25:41.957
- you always decide that you're fat.
- I am fat.

485
00:25:42.041 --> 00:25:45.294
I'm disgusting. and fat. and awful
and I don't deserve to live.

486
00:25:45.377 --> 00:25:47.463
Stop being mean to my best friend.

487
00:25:53.218 --> 00:25:55.637
You're the most beautiful person
I've ever met.

488
00:25:56.513 --> 00:25:58.182
even before you got thin.

489
00:26:00.809 --> 00:26:01.852
I don't see it.

490
00:26:03.520 --> 00:26:07.149
Sometimes other people see things
in you that you can't see for yourself.

491
00:26:11.862 --> 00:26:13.322
Everyone thinks I'm gay.

492
00:26:15.199 --> 00:26:17.785
Including Donald Choi.
who I made out with.

493
00:26:18.535 --> 00:26:21.038
Wait. you made out with Choi?
You're not gay.

494
00:26:21.121 --> 00:26:23.791
And besides.
nobody knows you better than me.

495
00:26:23.874 --> 00:26:26.293
If you were gay. I would know. trust me.

496
00:26:30.881 --> 00:26:32.007
Trust me.

497
00:26:32.841 --> 00:26:34.468
You look amazing in that bikini.

498
00:26:36.470 --> 00:26:37.638
You should buy it.

499
00:26:48.315 --> 00:26:51.693
<i>I was willing to do whatever it took
to win Coralee back.</i>

500
00:26:51.777 --> 00:26:55.739
<i>even if it meant taking a meeting
with Bob Boy Barbie Barnard.</i>

501
00:26:56.907 --> 00:26:59.493
Do you have to do that right now?

502
00:26:59.576 --> 00:27:01.245
Sorry. When you said
you were gonna be late.

503
00:27:01.328 --> 00:27:03.580
I thought I could squeeze in
a quick workout.

504
00:27:04.748 --> 00:27:07.209
We need to talk about Christian Keene.

505
00:27:07.292 --> 00:27:11.088
Don't need to spend time or money going
to court. he's a first time offender.

506
00:27:11.171 --> 00:27:14.049
I'm happy to settle
for a nominal fine. probation.

507
00:27:14.133 --> 00:27:15.676
Absolutely.

508
00:27:15.926 --> 00:27:17.845
No reason to destroy two lives.

509
00:27:19.471 --> 00:27:20.597
Who's the other one?

510
00:27:21.140 --> 00:27:23.433
- Magnolia.
- What are you talking about?

511
00:27:23.517 --> 00:27:25.727
She's one of his clients.

512
00:27:25.811 --> 00:27:29.523
There is no way
that Magnolia is a drug user.

513
00:27:29.606 --> 00:27:31.024
She's a straight-A student.

514
00:27:31.608 --> 00:27:36.697
Well. have you noticed
any changes in her behavior recently?

515
00:27:40.159 --> 00:27:42.661
She has been saying that
she's over doing pageants.

516
00:27:43.662 --> 00:27:44.663
Classic sign.

517
00:27:45.164 --> 00:27:48.625
Apathy. losing interest
in something you used to love.

518
00:27:49.251 --> 00:27:52.421
If Christian's selling drugs.
he's a danger to all our kids.

519
00:27:52.504 --> 00:27:54.631
He should be behind bars.
I'm not settling.

520
00:27:54.715 --> 00:27:56.175
He's going to jail.

521
00:27:56.758 --> 00:27:59.803
Oh...

522
00:28:00.262 --> 00:28:03.599
My client will be so disappointed.

523
00:28:04.516 --> 00:28:05.851
You heard from Coralee?

524
00:28:06.935 --> 00:28:07.936
What?

525
00:28:08.645 --> 00:28:09.855
- Why?
- Eh...

526
00:28:09.938 --> 00:28:10.939
She called me.

527
00:28:11.023 --> 00:28:15.777
Said she needed a place to stay
while the two of you "figured things out."

528
00:28:15.861 --> 00:28:17.487
- She called you?
- Mm.

529
00:28:17.988 --> 00:28:19.531
Is she staying at your house?

530
00:28:19.615 --> 00:28:20.490
No.

531
00:28:20.574 --> 00:28:23.368
Let's just say I have some real estate.

532
00:28:23.994 --> 00:28:28.373
But she made me promise not to tell you
where she is and I respect her.

533
00:28:28.457 --> 00:28:30.000
Don't worry. she's safe.

534
00:28:30.292 --> 00:28:33.045
Now that she has a real man
looking out for her.

535
00:28:35.255 --> 00:28:36.715
Where is she?

536
00:28:38.300 --> 00:28:39.384
Easy. Bob.

537
00:28:41.762 --> 00:28:43.180
Fuck you. Bob.

538
00:28:43.555 --> 00:28:46.850
<i>Coralee had the gall to ask me
to compromise my ethics</i>

539
00:28:46.934 --> 00:28:51.730
<i>after she had gone to the one person
she knew I hated the most?</i>

540
00:28:51.980 --> 00:28:53.941
<i>It felt like a kick in the nuts.</i>

541
00:28:54.942 --> 00:28:58.278
<i>Forget throwing the case.
Coralee would have to understand.</i>

542
00:28:58.362 --> 00:29:00.530
<i>I couldn't abandon my pageant dreams.</i>

543
00:29:00.614 --> 00:29:04.493
<i>If I wanted a chance at being a winner.
I needed to find a way to help Patty.</i>

544
00:29:08.163 --> 00:29:10.874
You can wait in here.
My dad should be home any minute.

545
00:29:11.583 --> 00:29:12.417
Thanks.

546
00:29:15.587 --> 00:29:18.340
Listen. I know you talked to my dad
behind my back.

547
00:29:18.423 --> 00:29:19.841
That's not cool.

548
00:29:19.925 --> 00:29:21.426
I'm sorry.

549
00:29:22.636 --> 00:29:24.888
I just thought it was so messed up.
what you told me.

550
00:29:24.972 --> 00:29:27.975
And you made things worse.
He told me a bunch of inappropriate shit.

551
00:29:28.058 --> 00:29:31.019
It was just the most
uncomfortable conversation ever.

552
00:29:31.478 --> 00:29:33.939
At least a bad conversation
is better than no conversation.

553
00:29:35.357 --> 00:29:38.443
I'm not trying to defend myself.
I'm just saying I've never met my dad.

554
00:29:38.527 --> 00:29:40.237
So at least you two were talking.

555
00:29:40.320 --> 00:29:43.115
And I would give anything
for one conversation with him.

556
00:29:43.198 --> 00:29:44.783
even an uncomfortable one.

557
00:29:46.034 --> 00:29:49.288
But that doesn't give me the right to
get all up in your business and I'm sorry.

558
00:29:49.371 --> 00:29:51.999
No. I'm sorry... about your dad.

559
00:29:52.082 --> 00:29:54.251
And I appreciate you
sticking up for me like that.

560
00:29:55.585 --> 00:29:59.339
I mean. you may have
actually helped. so...

561
00:30:01.383 --> 00:30:02.217
thank you.

562
00:30:06.221 --> 00:30:08.015
Do you want me
to sit with you while you wait?

563
00:30:08.098 --> 00:30:10.017
Or I could get you a soda. or...?

564
00:30:10.100 --> 00:30:13.145
Hey. Brick. Patty. I'm glad you're here.

565
00:30:14.604 --> 00:30:18.066
I'll. uh. let you two
get down to business.

566
00:30:22.487 --> 00:30:24.990
I want to help you get back
into Miss Magic Jesus.

567
00:30:26.742 --> 00:30:28.410
So. you're not still mad at me?

568
00:30:28.493 --> 00:30:30.829
I am. I'm just more mad at Coralee.

569
00:30:30.912 --> 00:30:32.122
Why? What did she do?

570
00:30:33.457 --> 00:30:34.499
It doesn't matter.

571
00:30:34.583 --> 00:30:37.753
From now on.
my personal life is off limits to you.

572
00:30:38.211 --> 00:30:40.505
The point is.
I want to win Christian's case.

573
00:30:40.589 --> 00:30:43.300
Great. Then he'll help me figure out
who hacked my phone.

574
00:30:43.383 --> 00:30:46.136
Now that I'm planning my bikini dog wash.
I'll look better to the board.

575
00:30:46.219 --> 00:30:47.304
Your bikini what?

576
00:30:47.387 --> 00:30:49.848
- Dog wash.
- What? Is that even a thing?

577
00:30:49.931 --> 00:30:52.267
It's a charity event
to add to my pageant resume.

578
00:30:52.351 --> 00:30:55.062
Why didn't you tell me I needed
a philanthropy to win Miss Magic Jesus?

579
00:30:55.145 --> 00:30:57.689
'Cause I was a little busy
proving you weren't a murderer

580
00:30:57.773 --> 00:31:00.359
and keeping you from ending up face down
in a puddle of chocolate!

581
00:31:02.944 --> 00:31:04.696
So. you'll win Christian's case?

582
00:31:04.780 --> 00:31:06.490
I've said I wanted to.

583
00:31:06.573 --> 00:31:10.118
The problem is. now Barnard knows
Christian sold drugs to Magnolia.

584
00:31:10.202 --> 00:31:12.037
He won't stop
till Christian is behind bars.

585
00:31:12.120 --> 00:31:13.580
But Christian said he wasn't dealing.

586
00:31:13.663 --> 00:31:16.291
Can't you get Magnolia to testify
he was just holding them for her?

587
00:31:17.751 --> 00:31:18.835
No.

588
00:31:18.919 --> 00:31:21.713
But you may have just figured out
a way to keep Christian out of jail.

589
00:31:24.174 --> 00:31:27.886
Why are you helping Patty Bladell with
her stupid eating disorder fundraiser?

590
00:31:27.969 --> 00:31:30.347
You are a horrible gremlin. Please leave.

591
00:31:32.516 --> 00:31:34.142
That bikini makes you look fat.

592
00:31:38.563 --> 00:31:40.065
Dixie. what part of...?

593
00:31:40.273 --> 00:31:41.566
What the hell are these?

594
00:31:43.402 --> 00:31:45.028
You can't search my room
without a warrant.

595
00:31:45.112 --> 00:31:48.573
I certainly can. as your father.
Are you doing this to get back at me?

596
00:31:49.533 --> 00:31:50.492
For what?

597
00:31:50.951 --> 00:31:53.328
Forcing me to do pageants
when I told you I was done?

598
00:31:53.912 --> 00:31:55.956
Inviting a pocket-sized Satan
to live in our house.

599
00:31:56.039 --> 00:31:58.417
without considering for one second
how that might affect me?

600
00:31:58.500 --> 00:32:01.711
Or for not telling me that my boyfriend
was cheating on me?

601
00:32:01.795 --> 00:32:03.839
No. do not turn this around.

602
00:32:03.922 --> 00:32:06.299
This is serious.
You are screwing up your life.

603
00:32:06.383 --> 00:32:09.261
Don't you mean
I'm screwing up your reputation?

604
00:32:09.344 --> 00:32:11.721
- This isn't about me.
- Of course it is.

605
00:32:11.805 --> 00:32:15.100
I am so tired
of having to be perfect all the time.

606
00:32:17.144 --> 00:32:19.771
I can't make a mistake.
I can't get a bad grade.

607
00:32:19.855 --> 00:32:23.316
I can't even leave my room without
looking like I'm off to a fashion shoot.

608
00:32:23.400 --> 00:32:26.403
I am so over being Magnolia Barnard.

609
00:32:34.578 --> 00:32:36.163
All right. I understand.

610
00:32:37.581 --> 00:32:43.128
It's hard having to keep up
the Barnard image all the time.

611
00:32:44.004 --> 00:32:46.256
And mom is away from home so much.

612
00:32:47.132 --> 00:32:49.092
Come on. we got to be a team. huh?

613
00:32:49.426 --> 00:32:51.595
Come on. Come here.

614
00:32:52.345 --> 00:32:54.139
I'm here for you. Magnolia.

615
00:32:54.848 --> 00:33:00.520
Okay? And I promise. we will win
Miss Magic Jesus and Miss American Lady

616
00:33:00.604 --> 00:33:02.606
and then we'll get you
whatever help you need.

617
00:33:02.689 --> 00:33:05.025
Hmm?

618
00:33:05.108 --> 00:33:06.193
Who's that?

619
00:33:08.820 --> 00:33:12.073
I got to go take care of this. sweetheart.
but I'm glad we talked.

620
00:33:18.455 --> 00:33:21.082
What's this about?
You gonna try to beat me up again?

621
00:33:21.500 --> 00:33:24.836
Oh. no. I am sorry about that.

622
00:33:24.920 --> 00:33:28.924
And since you were kind enough
to give me the heads up about Coralee.

623
00:33:29.007 --> 00:33:31.301
I wanted to give you a heads up
about Magnolia.

624
00:33:31.384 --> 00:33:32.469
- Another one?
- Mm-hm.

625
00:33:32.552 --> 00:33:36.973
I've complied a short list of witnesses
for Christian Keene's case

626
00:33:37.057 --> 00:33:39.684
and I wanted to warn ya.
Magnolia is on it.

627
00:33:40.936 --> 00:33:41.770
Wait. what?

628
00:33:41.853 --> 00:33:45.565
Well. Christian insists that
he was holding drugs for her...

629
00:33:45.649 --> 00:33:48.568
and that makes her the only person
that can attest to the fact that

630
00:33:48.652 --> 00:33:50.570
he didn't have any intent to distribute.

631
00:33:50.654 --> 00:33:52.656
Now you said he sold her those drugs.

632
00:33:52.739 --> 00:33:55.367
Do you really want her
to say that from the stand?

633
00:33:56.117 --> 00:33:59.996
I know how damaging that can be.
what with Miss Magic Jesus coming up.

634
00:34:00.080 --> 00:34:03.083
but some things are not preventable.

635
00:34:03.291 --> 00:34:06.169
So. I just wanted to let you know.

636
00:34:06.253 --> 00:34:09.839
'cause I know you would do
the same thing for me.

637
00:34:10.632 --> 00:34:11.841
Mm-hm.

638
00:34:13.051 --> 00:34:16.555
What would you say to a nominal fine
and community service?

639
00:34:18.306 --> 00:34:20.767
What do you mean. you can't figure out
who hacked Patty's phone?

640
00:34:20.850 --> 00:34:22.310
That was your end of the deal!

641
00:34:22.394 --> 00:34:24.563
I'm sorry. it's a sophisticated hack.

642
00:34:24.646 --> 00:34:28.149
Whoever had it out for Patty
is some kind of criminal mastermind.

643
00:34:28.233 --> 00:34:30.193
Ugh. Bullshit. you played me.

644
00:34:30.819 --> 00:34:32.696
Maybe you shouldn't have trusted
a drug dealer.

645
00:34:34.656 --> 00:34:35.991
I can't believe you.

646
00:34:36.533 --> 00:34:38.702
You took advantage of me
because you knew I liked you.

647
00:34:38.785 --> 00:34:39.911
I didn't know...

648
00:34:41.663 --> 00:34:42.706
until now.

649
00:34:43.665 --> 00:34:45.417
Thanks for keeping me out of jail.

650
00:34:50.255 --> 00:34:52.632
There has to be another way
to figure out who hacked my phone.

651
00:34:52.716 --> 00:34:55.302
Maybe there is. Christian is right.

652
00:34:55.385 --> 00:34:58.096
There is at least one criminal
who has it out for you.

653
00:34:58.179 --> 00:35:00.515
Or. more accurately. for us.

654
00:35:02.601 --> 00:35:03.685
Regina.

655
00:35:03.768 --> 00:35:08.607
Now. she is no mastermind. but she is
certainly in jail surrounded by a few.

656
00:35:09.190 --> 00:35:12.027
I can call over there
and see if Regina's in close proximity

657
00:35:12.110 --> 00:35:13.862
to any tech-savvy criminals.

658
00:35:19.326 --> 00:35:22.621
Oh. I like that.
Oh. I like that a lot.

659
00:35:24.331 --> 00:35:26.374
Wait. what are you...?

660
00:35:27.667 --> 00:35:28.752
Hello?

661
00:35:30.545 --> 00:35:31.713
It's for you.

662
00:35:32.005 --> 00:35:35.759
Oh! I hope you don't mind.
I gave my daughter this number.

663
00:35:36.176 --> 00:35:38.011
- Hello.
- Hi. Mama.

664
00:35:38.094 --> 00:35:40.388
Hi. baby. How's everything going?

665
00:35:40.472 --> 00:35:41.723
Not good.

666
00:35:41.806 --> 00:35:44.267
Everyone's been talking about my wigwam.

667
00:35:44.351 --> 00:35:46.936
<i>Well. what did you think would happen?</i>

668
00:35:47.020 --> 00:35:49.814
Sending out that picture was your idea.

669
00:35:49.898 --> 00:35:52.567
Yeah. to get Patty disqualified.

670
00:35:52.651 --> 00:35:55.195
But I figured everyone
would just think I'm a slut.

671
00:35:55.278 --> 00:35:58.073
Now they think I'm a lesbian
and that's way worse.

672
00:35:58.156 --> 00:35:59.949
Oh. honey.

673
00:36:00.283 --> 00:36:02.494
Everyone's a little gay.

674
00:36:02.744 --> 00:36:05.163
Besides. you should be grateful.

675
00:36:05.246 --> 00:36:08.708
It is a gift from God that my cellmate
happens to be a cyber-terrorist

676
00:36:08.792 --> 00:36:11.961
and she was able to hack
into Patty's phone.

677
00:36:12.587 --> 00:36:16.966
And you have no idea
what she made me do for payment.

678
00:36:20.095 --> 00:36:21.096
<i>Sorry. baby. I got to run.</i>

679
00:36:23.390 --> 00:36:24.224
Four.

680
00:36:24.766 --> 00:36:25.684
Five!

681
00:36:26.226 --> 00:36:27.102
- Six.
- Shelby!

682
00:36:27.185 --> 00:36:28.353
Got you a visitor.

683
00:36:29.646 --> 00:36:30.480
Done.

684
00:36:31.106 --> 00:36:34.442
<i>I pulled a favor with one of
the ladies who works admin at the prison.</i>

685
00:36:34.526 --> 00:36:36.736
<i>We swapped fashion tips for information.</i>

686
00:36:37.570 --> 00:36:40.990
<i>Lo and behold.
there was a cyber-terrorist in residence</i>

687
00:36:41.074 --> 00:36:46.246
<i>who happened to be cellmates
with none other than Regina Sinclair.</i>

688
00:36:46.871 --> 00:36:47.831
I'm Bob Armstrong.

689
00:36:49.999 --> 00:36:53.253
I. uh... I'm pretty sure
there's no touching allowed.

690
00:36:53.336 --> 00:36:54.796
But Ramon likes to watch.

691
00:36:55.630 --> 00:36:59.342
I've had my tired-of-bars and convicted-
to-love profiles up for over a year

692
00:36:59.426 --> 00:37:02.137
and I even hacked myself
onto the front page of both.

693
00:37:02.220 --> 00:37:04.264
and you're the first man to respond.

694
00:37:05.056 --> 00:37:06.725
Actually. I'm an attorney.

695
00:37:06.808 --> 00:37:08.017
Oh. well. good for you.

696
00:37:08.101 --> 00:37:09.644
Ramon. get us in the mood.

697
00:37:10.145 --> 00:37:13.231
Wait. what are you doing? Stop! Stop it!

698
00:37:13.857 --> 00:37:16.484
You want to peel the banana yourself?
That's even hotter.

699
00:37:16.568 --> 00:37:17.777
No. No peeling!

700
00:37:18.653 --> 00:37:20.238
I am here on business.

701
00:37:20.321 --> 00:37:22.198
- This isn't a conjugal?
- No.

702
00:37:24.033 --> 00:37:28.413
I know you hacked my client's cell phone
on behalf of Regina Sinclair.

703
00:37:28.496 --> 00:37:31.875
It is only a matter of time
before I have proof.

704
00:37:31.958 --> 00:37:33.960
Well. good luck with that.

705
00:37:34.043 --> 00:37:36.546
'Cause I'm a hacker.
I always cover my tracks.

706
00:37:36.629 --> 00:37:38.548
Shelby. I need your help.

707
00:37:38.965 --> 00:37:43.011
Those photos have wreaked havoc
on an innocent young girl's life.

708
00:37:43.094 --> 00:37:44.888
I used to be young too.

709
00:37:44.971 --> 00:37:46.723
And now I'm drying up like a prune.

710
00:37:46.806 --> 00:37:49.017
I might be able to help with that.

711
00:37:49.100 --> 00:37:50.894
That is. if you confess.

712
00:37:50.977 --> 00:37:52.812
I can't confess.

713
00:37:52.896 --> 00:37:56.191
I only got two weeks left on my sentence.
I can't risk not getting out.

714
00:37:56.775 --> 00:37:59.068
What if you pinned it on Regina Sinclair?

715
00:37:59.861 --> 00:38:01.738
And then you'll give me what I want?

716
00:38:04.491 --> 00:38:06.868
<i>I wasn't sure
I could go through with it.</i>

717
00:38:07.368 --> 00:38:10.246
<i>But my pageant-coaching future
was at stake.</i>

718
00:38:10.914 --> 00:38:13.541
<i>So. I did what I had to do.</i>

719
00:38:17.253 --> 00:38:18.713
I look like a lady.

720
00:38:19.255 --> 00:38:20.381
Give me your burner.

721
